                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "value": ", I've been looking into leaning how to do multithreaded programming in Rust. The scenario I have in mind is to split the render buffer into tiles and let separate threads render each time, where the number of worker threads is a variable.",
                                "position": {
                                    "start": {
                                        "line": 14,
                                        "column": 66,
                                        "offset": 420
                                    },
                                    "end": {
                                        "line": 14,
                                        "column": 305,
                                        "offset": 659
                                    },
                                    "indent": []
                                }
                            }
                        ],
                        "position": {
                            "start": {
                                "line": 14,
                                "column": 1,
                                "offset": 355
                            },
                            "end": {
                                "line": 14,
                                "column": 305,
                                "offset": 659
                            },
                            "indent": []
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "paragraph",
                        "children": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "value": "This requires some mechanism where a pool of threads is created, the tiles are dispatched to the threads awaiting work (i.e. some simple ",
                                "position": {
                                    "start": {
                                        "line": 16,
                                        "column": 1,
                                        "offset": 661
                                    },
                                    "end": {
                                        "line": 16,
                                        "column": 138,
                                        "offset": 798
                                    },
                                    "indent": []
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "title": null,
                                "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scheduling_(computing)#Scheduling_disciplines",
                                "children": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "value": "scheduling algorithm",
                                        "position": {
                                            "start": {
                                                "line": 16,
                                                "column": 139,
                                                "offset": 799
                                            },
                                            "end": {
                                                "line": 16,
                                                "column": 159,
                                                "offset": 819
                                            },
                                            "indent": []
                                        }
                                    }
                                ],
                                "position": {
                                    "start": {
                                        "line": 16,
                                        "column": 138,
                                        "offset": 798
                                    },
                                    "end": {
                                        "line": 16,
                                        "column": 237,
                                        "offset": 897
                                    },
                                    "indent": []
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "value": "), the tiles then rendered to a memory buffer, that then is passed back to the main thread to be copied into the main buffer.",
                                "position": {
